HEADWORD: Lepidosiren
<hw>Lep`i*do*si"ren</hw> <pr>(-s⟦imac⟧"r⟦ecr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>lepi`s</grk> <grk>-i`dos</grk>, a scale +
<grk>seirh`n</grk> a siren.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An eel-shaped
ganoid fish of the order Dipnoi, having both gills and lungs. It
inhabits the rivers of South America. The name is also applied to a
related African species (<spn>Protopterus annectens</spn>). The
lepidosirens grow to a length of from four to six feet. Called also
<altname>doko</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

